I move short specific threads to their appropriate forum, I move long specific threads that have aged past the first page of GENERAL to their specific forum.  I lock threads that are flames, or short redundant threads, and I always explain my reasons.  I edit subjects for clarity, messages for profanity, or to activate EZCodes when the author clearly intended their use, i.e. a message that contains uninterpreted but properly formed tags.<br>
<br>
I am strongly against <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">anything</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> that stifles debate in this forum, and the number one culprit in this regard is not the moderators, but those posters who insist on insulting, demeaning, ridiculing, or otherwise denigrating those who disagree with them.  Anyone who clearly crosses that line gets taken to task, whether it is <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Wezloc, Noonie, Rthen, Galerius, Rhion</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> or whomever.<br>
